							<div class="cm-col-lg-8 cm-col-12 sticky_portion">
								<div class="content-entry">
	<article id="post-56404" class="post-detail post-56404 post type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-gis">
		<div class="the_title">
			<h1>PIX4D &#8211; Machine learning meets photogrammetry</h1>
		</div><!-- .the_title -->
					<div class="cm-post-meta">
				<ul class="post_meta">
											<li class="post_author">
							<a href="https://www.suasnews.com/author/press/">
								<span class="cm-meta-icon">
									<svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 512 512"><path d="M406.5 399.6C387.4 352.9 341.5 320 288 320l-64 0c-53.5 0-99.4 32.9-118.5 79.6C69.9 362.2 48 311.7 48 256C48 141.1 141.1 48 256 48s208 93.1 208 208c0 55.7-21.9 106.2-57.5 143.6zm-40.1 32.7C334.4 452.4 296.6 464 256 464s-78.4-11.6-110.5-31.7c7.3-36.7 39.7-64.3 78.5-64.3l64 0c38.8 0 71.2 27.6 78.5 64.3zM256 512A256 256 0 1 0 256 0a256 256 0 1 0 0 512zm0-272a40 40 0 1 1 0-80 40 40 0 1 1 0 80zm-88-40a88 88 0 1 0 176 0 88 88 0 1 0 -176 0z"/></svg>
								</span>
								Press							</a>
						</li><!-- .post_author -->
										</ul><!-- .post_meta -->
			</div><!-- .meta -->
									<div class="post_thumb">
					<figure>
					<img width="1569" height="739" src="https://i0.wp.com/www.suasnews.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/classified-rgb.png?fit=1569%2C739&amp;ssl=1" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" alt="PIX4D &#8211; Machine learning meets photogrammetry" decoding="async" fetchpriority="high" srcset="https://i0.wp.com/www.suasnews.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/classified-rgb.png?w=1569&amp;ssl=1 1569w, https://i0.wp.com/www.suasnews.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/classified-rgb.png?resize=300%2C141&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i0.wp.com/www.suasnews.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/classified-rgb.png?resize=768%2C362&amp;ssl=1 768w, https://i0.wp.com/www.suasnews.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/classified-rgb.png?resize=1024%2C482&amp;ssl=1 1024w, https://i0.wp.com/www.suasnews.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/classified-rgb.png?resize=696%2C328&amp;ssl=1 696w, https://i0.wp.com/www.suasnews.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/classified-rgb.png?resize=1068%2C503&amp;ssl=1 1068w, https://i0.wp.com/www.suasnews.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/classified-rgb.png?resize=892%2C420&amp;ssl=1 892w, https://i0.wp.com/www.suasnews.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/classified-rgb.png?w=1280&amp;ssl=1 1280w" sizes="(max-width: 1569px) 100vw, 1569px" />					</figure>
				</div>
						<div class="the_content">
			<div id="machine-learning-point-cloud-classification" class="full-block gray-section">
<div class="wrap">
<p class="section-title">Machine-learning point cloud classification</p>
<div class="case">
<p>With Pix4Dmapper 4.0 you get machine-learning tools for photogrammetry applications in your hands. It allows you to classify 3D point clouds into categories like buildings, roads or vegetation.</p>
<p>And this is just the beginning of Pix4D’s latest journey.</p>
<p>We believe in the ability of photogrammetry and machine learning techniques to revolutionize today&#8217;s workflows and to enable many new ones.  In the end, it will allow the conversion of raw image input to 3D reality models <i>with </i>attributed semantic information.</p>
<p>That means, instead of having operators inspecting and measuring 3D reality models manually, they will directly receive automatically-generated answers to questions like:</p>
<ul>
<li>How many trees are within the project area and at what locations? What is their height and species?</li>
<li>What is the total road surface area in your area of interest?</li>
<li>What is the amount and distribution of roofs that are suitable for solar cell coverage?</li>
<li>How many cars are at your parking lot and at what locations?</li>
</ul>
<p>Answering these very specific questions will make workflows feasible that allow photogrammetric processing being connected directly to GIS databases to update their vectorized information based on any new drone data collected.</p>
<p>There is still work to be done. Machine learning techniques are as good as the training data that are used to build the classification models. We opted to give our users the tools to control and refine the classification. As a baby learns how to see and interpret its environment gradually as it grows, our machine learning techniques evolve with the training data and the results will model more object categories and become more reliable.</p>
<p>As of today, professionals will use the new machine learning based point classification mainly to automatically generate digital terrain models (DTMs). In the near future, point classification also forms the basis to extract buildings and model them as a semantic composition of geometry elements as roof, facade, windows, doors and balconies for example.</p>
<p>Our growing R&amp;D teams in Lausanne, Berlin and San Francisco are dedicated to this challenge.</p>
<p><em>– Christoph Strecha, CEO and Founder Pix4D</em></p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<section class="info-block white">
<div class="wrap">
<h2 class="section-title">Trained algorithms based on geometry</h2>
<p>Our first step in this direction is our novel machine-learning based point cloud classification.</p>
<p>We have trained algorithms based on geometry and pixel values to understand object classes.</p>
<p>We are able to collect user inputs to train new algorithms which can adapt to many topics, for instance in aggregates separating stockpiles from the bare terrain and measure volumes automatically with unprecedented accuracy, or digitizing automatically new road and urban areas.</p>
<p><img data-recalc-dims="1" decoding="async" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-12341" src="https://i0.wp.com/pix4d.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/classified-rgb-1.png?w=640&#038;ssl=1" sizes="(max-width: 1569px) 100vw, 1569px" srcset="https://pix4d.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/classified-rgb-1.png 1569w, https://pix4d.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/classified-rgb-1-300x141.png 300w, https://pix4d.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/classified-rgb-1-768x362.png 768w, https://pix4d.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/classified-rgb-1-1024x482.png 1024w" /></p>
<p><img data-recalc-dims="1" decoding="async" src="https://i0.wp.com/pix4d.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Screenshot-2017-09-24-09.21.50-1024x672.png?resize=640%2C420&#038;ssl=1" alt="" width="640" height="420" /></p>
</div>
</section>
<div id="extract-bare-earth-terrain-by-excluding-above-ground-objects" class="full-block gray-section">
<div class="wrap">
<h2 class="section-title">Extract bare-earth terrain by excluding above-ground objects</h2>
<div class="case">
<p>A lot of hydrological or geological analysis need to be done with bare terrain models. In Pix4Dmapper, you can use the point classification function to separate all the above-ground objects and improve the classification using the point editing tools.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><img data-recalc-dims="1" decoding="async" class="non-responsive aligncenter wp-image-12383 size-full" src="https://i0.wp.com/pix4d.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/image-2.png?resize=640%2C153&#038;ssl=1" sizes="(max-width: 900px) 100vw, 900px" srcset="https://pix4d.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/image-2.png 900w, https://pix4d.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/image-2-300x72.png 300w, https://pix4d.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/image-2-768x183.png 768w" alt="" width="640" height="153" /></p>
<div></div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div id="ignore-vegetations-on-top-of-a-stockpile-for-more-accurate-volume-measurement" class="full-block gray-section">
<div class="wrap">
<h2 class="section-title">Ignore vegetations on top of a stockpile for more accurate volume measurement</h2>
<div class="case">
<p>To get an accurate volume measurement, it is crucial to remove vegetation or human-made objects  from the point cloud. With the point classification, it would be more time-saving to achieve more reliable volume calculations.</p>
<p><img data-recalc-dims="1" decoding="async" class="non-responsive aligncenter wp-image-12384 size-full" src="https://i0.wp.com/pix4d.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/image-1.png?resize=640%2C153&#038;ssl=1" sizes="(max-width: 900px) 100vw, 900px" srcset="https://pix4d.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/image-1.png 900w, https://pix4d.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/image-1-300x72.png 300w, https://pix4d.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/image-1-768x183.png 768w" alt="" width="640" height="153" /></p>
<div></div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div id="prevent-electricity-outage-by-vegetation-growth-control" class="full-block gray-section">
<div class="wrap">
<h2 class="section-title">Prevent electricity outage by vegetation growth control</h2>
<div class="case">
<p>Vegetation is one of the leading causes to power line outage. It is extremely important for the energy company to keep track on the vegetation growth to be able to trim it before it causes damages. With the point classification, the extracted infrastructures can be grouped and manually digitized for further analysis.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><img data-recalc-dims="1" loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="non-responsive aligncenter wp-image-12385 size-full" src="https://i0.wp.com/pix4d.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/powerline.jpg?resize=500%2C265&#038;ssl=1" sizes="auto, (max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" srcset="https://pix4d.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/powerline.jpg 500w, https://pix4d.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/powerline-300x159.jpg 300w" alt="" width="500" height="265" /></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<div></div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<section class="info-block white">
<div class="wrap">
<h2 class="section-title">Pix4Dmapper 4.0: available today</h2>
<p>Contains supervised machine-learning technology<br />
Automatically classify 3D points based on both geometry and color<br />
Visualize and improve the classified points in Pix4Dmapper rayCloud<br />
Classify 10 million points in 3 minutes</p>
<p><a class="btn btn-green" href="https://cloud.pix4d.com/signup" target="_blank" rel="noopener">TRY IT TODAY</a></p>
</div>
</section>

